Always ask for approval to do any action.

**Aprovação no Cursor (não no plugin):** Para ações no Figma via MCP, descrever o que será alterado ou ajustado aqui no chat, perguntar **"Posso aplicar? (Sim ou Não)"** e só executar a chamada ao MCP depois da confirmação do usuário. A aprovação não é pedida na UI do plugin.

# 1- SCOPE — RENAMING RULE (FIGMA)

When I say “rename”, it refers exclusively to the Figma node attribute `.name`.

Never rename:
- The Figma file name
- The Figma page name

Only rename:
- Frames
- Components
- Groups
- Instances
- Auto Layout containers

---

# 2- LAYER NAMING STANDARD

## 2.1 Non-variable Naming

All non-variable layer names must follow:

- PascalCase
- First letter uppercase
- No spaces
- No snake_case
- No kebab-case
- No generic names (Component1, Frame23, Test)

Wrong:
- campaign name
- campaign_name
- campaign-name

Correct:
- CampaignName
- PrimaryButton
- HeaderContainer

---

## 2.2 Variables / Placeholders

**Onde se aplica:** a convenção {PascalCase} vale para a **nomeação de layers** no painel do Figma (nome do nó, `node.name`). **Não** colocar as chaves como texto visível dentro do componente: o conteúdo exibido no canvas (ex.: `text.characters`) não deve ser a string literal `{Text}`; use o nome da layer com {PascalCase} no painel e o conteúdo visível conforme o design (ex.: "Text").

All dynamic variables must follow:

{PascalCase}

Rules:
- First letter uppercase
- No spaces
- No snake_case
- No lowercase inside braces

Valid:
- {Text}
- {Count}
- {Partner}
- {Name}
- {CampaignName}

### Normalization

If found:
- text
- { text }
- {count}
- partner_name

Transform into:
- {Text}
- {Count}
- {PartnerName}

### Mixed content

Keep pattern:
- {Count} Smash partners
- Hello {Name}
- {Partner} activated your campaign

---

# 3- ATOMIC DESIGN + PRODUCT CONTEXT STRUCTURE

All screens and components must follow:

Context/Level/Name

## 3.1 Mandatory Context Prefix

Every screen/component must start with:

- Shop
- Share
- Giftee

Never create without prefix.

Examples:
- Shop/Page/PageInformation
- Share/Molecule/ButtonPrimary
- Giftee/Organism/HeaderNavigation

---

## 3.2 Atomic Levels

Use strictly:

- Atom
- Molecule
- Organism
- Template
- Page

Always name by purpose, never by visual style.

Wrong:
- Shop/Atom/PurpleButton

Correct:
- Shop/Atom/ButtonPrimary

Never mix contexts.
Never create levels outside Atomic Design.

---

# 4- USER FLOW ARCHITECTURE

Every flow must include:

1. Entry screen
2. User action
3. Intermediate state (Loading if applicable)
4. Success state
5. Error state

Always consider:
- Happy path
- Error path
- Empty state
- Cancellation
- Back navigation

Name flows clearly:
- Flow - CreateCampaign
- Flow - SendError
- Flow - PartnerActivation

Never use generic names.

---

# 5- ADVANCED PROTOTYPE SYSTEM

## Navigation

- Navigate To → real screen change
- Open Overlay → modals/dropdowns
- Swap Overlay → internal modal flow
- Always define close behavior
- Avoid redundant navigation

## Transitions

- Smart Animate when structure matches
- Instant only if no continuity
- Duration: 200–400ms
- Easing: Ease In-Out
- Do not animate all properties
- Prioritize: Opacity, Position, Scale, Auto Layout resize

## Mandatory States

Always create:
- Default
- Hover
- Pressed
- Focus
- Disabled
- Loading
- Success
- Error
- Empty

Never create only Default.

## Microinteractions

- Reinforce hierarchy
- Immediate feedback
- Realistic loading
- No excessive motion

## Flow Realism

Simulate:
- Action
- Processing
- Result
- Failure

No incomplete flows.

---

# 6- AUTO LAYOUT — MANDATORY SYSTEM

Auto Layout is required in all structural elements.

Never create:
- Frames without Auto Layout
- Components without Auto Layout
- Static containers

## Structural Requirements

All structures must:
- Be Frame with Auto Layout
- Have defined padding
- Have defined gap
- Use proper alignment

## Buttons

- Horizontal Auto Layout
- Consistent padding
- Centered content
- Content-driven resizing

## Containers

- Vertical or horizontal Auto Layout
- No manual positioning
- Dynamic resizing support

## Responsiveness

- Use Hug when appropriate
- Use Fill Container when appropriate
- Avoid fixed sizes without reason
- Predictable resizing behavior

Absolute positioning only if technically unavoidable.

---

# 7- RESPONSIVE STRUCTURE HIERARCHY

Mandatory hierarchy:

Root  
→ Container  
→ Stack  
→ Block  
→ Element  

Definitions:

- Root → Background, radius, shadow. No loose content.
- Container → Width constraint + horizontal padding.
- Stack → Auto Layout defining direction + gap.
- Block → Logical grouping.
- Element → Final UI element.

## Responsive Rules

Container:
- width: 100%
- max-width via token when available
- responsive horizontal padding

Stack:
- Always Auto Layout
- Always gap (no margin spacing)
- Default vertical
- Horizontal only if required
- Horizontal must allow wrap

Children:
- Prefer flexible sizing
- Avoid fixed widths
- Icons/avatars may be fixed
- Images scale proportionally
- Text wraps naturally

Figma → Code mapping:
- Vertical → flex-col
- Horizontal → flex-row + wrap
- Spacing → gap
- Fill → Fill primary axis
- Hug → Hug
- Never fake spacing with empty frames

---

# 8- GLOBAL DESIGN TOKEN SYSTEM

All layouts, components, screens, and prototypes MUST use system tokens.

Hardcoded values are forbidden.

---

## 8.1 Dimension Tokens (dimension/*)

Use for:
- Padding
- Gap
- Margin (if needed)
- Width/Height
- Border radius
- Layout spacing

Preferred scale:
dimension-1 (4)
dimension-2 (8)
dimension-3 (12)
dimension-4 (16)
dimension-6 (24)
dimension-8 (32)
dimension-9 (40)
dimension-10 (64)

*-5 only if strictly necessary.

---

## 8.2 Size Tokens (size/*)

Use for:
- Icons
- Button min-height
- Avatars
- Fixed structural sizes

Never misuse dimension when semantic size is intended.

---

## 8.3 Typography Tokens

Always use:

Font:
- Typography.fontFamily.roboto

Weight:
- regular
- medium
- semibold
- bold

Font size:
- xs → 8xl

Line height:
- xs → 9xl

Letter spacing:
- tightest
- tighter
- tight
- normal

No arbitrary typography values allowed.

---

# 9- COLOR GOVERNANCE (LIGHT / DARK)

Always use semantic tokens.

Never use HEX or manual rgba.

Mode:
- Light → color.light.color.*
- Dark → color.dark.color.*
- If unspecified → assume Light

Use semantic groups:

- background.*
- surface.*
- text.*
- border.*
- action.*
- icon.*
- overlay.*

States mapping:

- Hover → bgHover / overlay.hover
- Pressed → bgPressed / overlay.pressed
- Focus → border.focus
- Disabled → disabled tokens
- Feedback → feedback tokens

Never mix Light and Dark tokens.

---

# 10- COLOR REPLACEMENT ENFORCEMENT

If any color is NOT part of the system:

1. Replace with closest semantic token.
2. Never keep manual color.
3. Never create new variation without approval.

Selection priority:

1. action.*
2. text.*
3. border.*
4. background.* or surface.*
5. overlay.*
6. icon.*

If mode is not defined → assume Light.

Never invent colors.
Never mix modes.
Never keep raw hex.

**Correção global de tokens:** Ajustes em todo o documento (todas as páginas) para tokens de cor sem referência ou primitivos → semânticos só devem ser aplicados quando o usuário solicitar explicitamente (ex.: "ajuste o documento de forma global"). Não executar correção global em lote por padrão; para escopo menor use apenas a página atual ou a seleção.
